definition.value: Sexual arousal from displaying of strength or of muscles.
A sexual obsession of a submissive with their dominant partner's penis; or any type of sexual game in which a submissive is motivated by a real or pretended attraction to their partner's penis.
A sexual fascination with the feminine in the form of the vagina, along with all the practices related to the deification of the female in relationship to the vagina.

A condition characterized by severe deprivation of basic human needs, including food, safe drinking water, sanitation facilities, health, shelter, education and information. It depends not only on income but also on access to services.

The complete lack of the means necessary to meet basic personal needs, such as food, clothing and shelter. The threshold at which absolute poverty is defined is always about the same, independent of the person's permanent location or era.
Pregnancy as a result of rape.

Poverty which occurs when a person cannot meet a minimum level of living standards, compared to others in the same time and place. Therefore, the threshold at which relative poverty is defined varies from one country to another, or from one society to another.
The condition of some part of one's anatomy being dilated or stretched.
Dilation of the anus.

The reflexive dilation of the human anus to a diameter greater than two centimeters in response to the parting of the buttocks or anal stimulation, such as brushing with a medical instrument. It has been theorized to be a clinical marker associated with anal sexual assault in children, and has been associated with other signs of sexual assault but also appears in children with severe chronic constipation and those subject to invasive medical treatments of the anus.

The distribution of sexually explicit images or video of individuals without their permission. The sexually explicit images or video may be made by a partner of an intimate relationship with the knowledge and consent of the subject, or it may be made without their knowledge. The possession of the material may be used by the perpetrators to blackmail the subjects into performing other sex acts, to coerce them into continuing the relationship, to punish them for ending the relationship, or to silence them.
Reflexes associated with the peripheral nervous system.
The reflexive contraction of the external anal sphincter upon stroking of the skin around the anus.
Any of various temporary insanity defenses involving a state of panic used to justify assault, manslaughter, or murder of LGBTQIA+ persons.
Politicians who are transgender.
Politicians who are bisexual.
Politicians who are intersex.

An ethnic group who live mainly in the West Nile region of Uganda and in the adjoining area of the Democratic Republic of the Congo (DRC). They speak the Lugbara language, a Central Sudanic language similar to the language spoken by the Madi, with whom they also share many cultural similarities. They are also found in South Sudan where they are known as Mundu and other names.

Native peoples of Kamchatka, Russia. The name Kamchadal was applied to the descendants of the local Siberians and aboriginal peoples (the Itelmens, Ainu, Koryaks and Chuvans), who assimilated with the Russians.

An ethnic group native to the Kamchatka Peninsula in Russia. The Itelmen language is distantly related to Chukchi and Koryak, forming the Chukotko-Kamchatkan language family, but it is now virtually extinct, the vast majority of ethnic Itelmens being native speakers of Russian.

A term usually used to refer to hijras living in north India; also used in other parts of India (such as Maharashtra) by hijra to refer to themselves. Some scholars consider the identity separate from hijra.

A gender categorization observed in a specific community in Andhra Pradesh. The term refers to those persons assigned male at birth who are possessed by or married to any of various gods, most notably Shiva. Shiv-shakthis generally present a feminine gender expression and appear as women during religious ceremonies and festivals.
Hijra in Maharashtra and Karnataka who devote themselves to the service of a particular god.
Kothi who devote themselves to the service of a particular god.
A term used to refer to hijra in Tamil Nadu. Some prefer the term thirunangi, which translates as "daughter of god".
"Aravani" may also be used broadly as a catch-all term for gender and sexual minorities in Tamil Nadu.
Hijra who have undergone nirvan, a ritual during which the testes, penis, and scrotum are removed.
Hijra who present as female but have not yet undergone nirvan (nirwaan), although they often intend to at some point.
Hijra who do not plan to undergo nirvan (nirwaan).

Kothi who have had their penis, scrotum, and testicles removed; alternatively, a term used in north India to refer to some persons assigned male at birth who have sex with men or with men and women, often these persons cross-dress, express themselves in a more feminine manner, and fulfill the role of penetrative partner in sexual relationships.
A polite term sometimes used in the place of hijra in Pakistan.
Gender activists in Pakistan have promoted khwaja sira as a politically correct alternative to hijra.
Note that this term was also used to refer to such persons who were employed as courtly or military leaders by the Mughal kingdoms in 17th and 18th century India.
A person who undergoes any of the various processes of menstruation.
People who menstruate include postmenarchal premenopausal cisgender women, some transgender men, and some assigned-female-at-birth (AFAB) nonbinary people, among other groups.
The science of behavior and mind. Psychology includes the study of conscious and unconscious phenomena, as well as feeling and thought.
The study of behavior and cognition.
A social science dealing with group relationships, patterns of collective behavior, and social organization.
The branch of psychology concerned with the effects of group membership upon the behavior, attitudes, and beliefs of an individual.
The branch of psychology that studies persons and their relationships with others and with groups and with society as a whole.
The scientific study of the nature, extent, management, causes, control, consequences, and prevention of criminal behavior, both on individual and social levels.
The study of crime and criminals with special reference to the personality factors and social conditions leading toward, or away from crime.
A subspeciality of psychiatry and is related to criminology. It encompasses the interface between law and psychiatry.
Psychiatry in its legal aspects.
A discipline concerned with the origin, structure, development, growth, function, genetics, and reproduction of animals, plants, and microorganisms.
The scientific study of living organisms.
A basic science concerned with the composition, structure, and properties of matter; and the reactions that occur between substances and the associated energy exchange.
The science of the composition, structure, properties, and reactions of matter, especially of atomic and molecular systems.
The branch of science concerned with origin and development of humans in all their physical, social, and cultural relationships.

A sociolinguistic model in which slang utilized in minority populations is assimilated into the "standard" language variant. For example, "shade" and "realness" being used exclusively in gay and transgender communities of color before being integrated into the gay white lexicon and then into the general "mainstream" lexicon.
The branch of social science that deals with the production and distribution and consumption of goods and services and their management.
The critical study of economics and economies, with a focus on gender-aware and inclusive economic inquiry and policy analysis.
A subfield of economics which seeks to understand the functioning and dynamics of the markets for wage labor.
Any of various rituals associated with reproduction.
Any of various rituals associated with fertility.
Any of various rituals associated with pregnancy.
Any of various rituals that the father adopts during the partner's pregnancy.
An autobiography about an LGBTQIA+ person's life.
Medical journals which cover urological topics.
Homicide of an LGBTQIA+ person in which the person's attitudes toward LGBTQIA+ persons ultimately resulted in the homicide.
